sense.name: collect and put together evidence, data, or information
sense.examples: We're compiling some facts and figures for a documentary on the subject. They compiled a survey containing reports from correspondents in 40 countries. Police compiled a report and advised them to cancel the stolen credit cards. He compiled encyclopedias of astronomy, scientific biography, chemistry, and physics.

sense.name: translate programming code into machine language using a compiler
sense.examples: Copy the file called Makefile into your directory and type 'make' to compile the program. Once the code was compiled normally, a command was used to run the test case. Always save your program before compiling.
